    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You hum a soothing melody and rub a bit of bear fur, inducing a soporific healing state in a creature you touch. The target regains 1d6 hit points and sleeps for 10 minutes per each hit point regained. If the creature is unwilling, it must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or fall asleep for the duration. At the end of each of its turns, the target can make another Constitution saving throw. On a success, the spell ends on the target.<br>Each creature affected by this spell falls unconscious until the spell ends, until the hibernating creature takes damage, or until a creature uses an action to shake or slap the hibernating creature awake. Undead and creatures immune to being charmed arenâ€™t affected by this spell.<br><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.<br>Content licensed under the @UUID[Compendium.koboldpressogl.koboldpressjournal.JournalEntry.KoboldPressOGL00.JournalEntryPage.KoboldPressOGLpg]{Open Game License}",
